"{\"correct\": \"no\", \"explanation\": \"The OneHotEncoder in scikit-learn does not directly support string input. It requires integer input. However, in this code, the column 'b' is of type object which contains strings. To fix this, we need to use the LabelEncoder or OrdinalEncoder before OneHotEncoder to convert the string labels into integer labels.\", \"patch\": \"20,21c20,21\\n< ('numeric', MinMaxScaler(), ['a']),\\n< ('categoric', OneHotEncoder(), [\\\"b\\\"])\\n---\\n> ('numeric', MinMaxScaler(), ['a']),\\n> ('categoric', Pipeline([('label', LabelEncoder()), ('onehot', OneHotEncoder())]), [\\\"b\\\"])\\n\"}"